            Hint
**********************************************-->


<!--*********************************************
            Solution
**********************************************-->  
<solution>
<ul>
    <li><p>First, solve for the common difference, <m>d</m>. Note that <m>$a5 - ($a4) = $d</m> and <m>$a4 - ($a3) = $d</m> and so on. Continuing this process, you can verify the difference between each pair of terms. We are looking at an arithmetic sequence with common difference <m>$d</m>.</p>
    </li>

    <li><p>The next term is found by adding the common difference, <m>$d</m>, to the last term shown. 
      <me>$a5 + $d = $sol</me></p>
    </li>
  </ul>
</solution>
</problem>


